# AdForge configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# install.bat / install.sh will create a real `.env.local` from this file
# and fill in your chosen port. You can also create `.env.local` by hand.
#
# Defaults are sensible — most users won't need to change anything.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Web app port. Defaults to 3005.
#   Open  http://localhost:3005/  in your browser
#   Or    http://adforge.localhost:3005/  (works in Chrome / Firefox / Safari / Edge
#         with NO setup — all modern browsers auto-resolve *.localhost to 127.0.0.1)
PORT=3005

# Local-sync sidecar port. Defaults to 3006. Bound to 127.0.0.1 only.
# Only change if you have a real conflict — the browser-side client is
# currently hardcoded to 3006, so changing this requires editing
# lib/local-sync.ts as well.
ADFORGE_SYNC_PORT=3006

# Optional friendly hostname.
# Leave commented out for the default (localhost).
# To use a custom hostname like  adforge.local  you need a hosts file entry:
#   Windows:    run  scripts\set-domain.bat  as Administrator
#   Mac/Linux:  run  bash scripts/set-domain.sh  with sudo
# After that, open  http://adforge.local:3005/  in your browser.
# See docs/CUSTOM_DOMAIN.md for details + the simpler *.localhost option.
# ADFORGE_HOSTNAME=adforge.local
